    "body": "I tried another simple contract which has shorter bytecode. This is contract code: \r\n```\r\npragma solidity 0.8.18;\r\ncontract Lock {\r\n    uint256 public unlockTime;\r\n    address payable public owner;\r\n    event Withdrawal(uint256 amount, uint256 when);\r\n\r\n    constructor(uint256 _unlockTime) payable {\r\n        require(block.timestamp < _unlockTime, \"Unlock time should be in the future\");\r\n        unlockTime = _unlockTime;\r\n        owner = payable(msg.sender);\r\n    }\r\n    function withdraw() public {\r\n        require(block.timestamp >= unlockTime, \"You can't withdraw yet\");\r\n        require(msg.sender == owner, \"You aren't the owner\");\r\n        emit Withdrawal(address(this).balance, block.timestamp);\r\n        owner.transfer(address(this).balance);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nHardhat compiled bytecode: \r\n```\r\\r\n```\r\n\r\nfoundry bytecode: \r\n```\r\\r\n```\r\n\r\nCompare:\r\n<img width=\"1471\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/assets/27964406/fa674e1d-4147-40e6-8a3f-fab5e764384b\">\r\n\r\n",
